mething like<br />&gt;<br />&gt; CONFIG_ARCH_SCALAR_ACCESS_ONCE be a good start?<br /><br />No, if it's just a handful of places to be fixed, let's not add config<br />options for broken cases.<br /><br />&gt; This would boil down to<br />&gt; Patch1: Provide stricter ACCESS_ONCE if CONFIG_ARCH_SCALAR_ACCESS_ONCE is set + docu update + comments<br />&gt; Patch2: Change mm/* to barriers<br />&gt; Patch3: Change x86 locks<br />&gt; Patch4: Change x86 gup<br />&gt; Patch4: Enable CONFIG_ARCH_SCALAR_ACCESS_ONCE for s390x and x86<br /><br />Just do patches 2-4 first, and then patch 1 unconditionally.<br /><br />Obviously you'd need to spread the word on linux-arch to see how bad<br />it is for other cases, but if other architectures are at all like x86<br />and s390, and just require a few trivial patches, let's not make this<br />some config option.<br /><br />                   Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
